
[1]tenacity

   TENAC'ITY, n. [L. tenacitas, from teneo, to hold.]

   1. Adhesiveness; that quality of bodies which makes them stick or
   adhere to others; glutinousness; stickiness; as the tenacity of oils,
   of glue, of tar, of starch and the like.

   2. That quality of bodies which keeps them from parting; without
   considerable force; cohesiveness; the effect of attraction; opposed to
   brittleness or fragility.
